# LifesaverOnCall — Project ISA

> Project ISA (system of record). Lives in the repo per PAI doctrine. Supersedes the `context/{facts,state,references,feedback}.md` foundation pattern: those files fold into the sections below and are retained as detailed appendices until fully absorbed. The `USER/PROJECTS/lifesaveroncall.md` entry in PAI is the lightweight index that points here.

## Problem

Manual paging and roster phone trees are slow and error-prone for SLSA volunteer lifesaver dispatch in emergency situations. Life Saving Victoria (LSV) operates without a map-first dispatch interface, proper de-identification, or real-time responder availability tracking. When a rescue is called, dispatchers must manually contact candidates rather than the system surfacing the closest available, award-current responders automatically.

## Vision

A GoodSAM-style emergency dispatch platform for SLSA volunteers: map-first dispatch that pages the closest available, award-eligible responders automatically; incident lifecycle management from callout creation through stand-down; and a mobile responder app for on-the-go accept/reject/navigation. Stage 1 targets LSV (Victoria) via LIMSOC credential integration; pluggable adapters are architected for other states later. Euphoric surprise: a dispatcher who previously relied on a phone tree finds the right responders paged and accepted within seconds, with a full audit trail and no PII leaked to the wrong people.

## Out of Scope

- National rollout beyond LSV in Stage 1 (pluggable adapter architectured, not built).
- SLSA OIDC client provisioning (FR-1.1 -- still pending external action from LSV).
- Apple Critical Alerts entitlement (deferred until product is proven and LSV affiliation letter obtained).
