- SaaS pricing model and multi-tenant commercial go-to-market (future stage).
- Branch protection on main/dev (requires GitHub Pro).

## Principles

- Safety is first: dispatch is life-critical. Never dispatch a member with an expired award or pending/suspended/not-approved capability status.
- User journey before code: write the 3-5 step responder/dispatcher journey and confirm before writing a line.
- Location is consent: location data is only collected and shared when a member is `available` or accepted on a callout.
- Identity reveal follows a six-rule precedence (KICKOFF.md §6): `unavailable` members are never visible, even with `view_member_pii`.
- Append-only incident log: log entries are never mutated; corrections are additional entries. Incomplete logs make debriefs and disputes unanswerable.
- Never treat Pub/Sub publish as delivery: subscribers must ack; DLQ with alerting is required.
- Critical alerts are reserved exclusively for the initial request-for-assistance push to candidate responders -- not stand-downs, status updates, or approvals.
- Fail closed on tenancy: every read query filters by tenant scope. Cross-org dispatch allowed only via explicit consent matrix.

## Constraints

- **Stack is settled:** Bun runtime; Hono API; Next.js 15 + React 19 (web); Expo + React Native + EAS (mobile); Postgres 16 + PostGIS via Cloud SQL; GCP Pub/Sub (emulator locally, real in prod); Redis cache; Docker Compose for local; Firebase Auth (email/password); Google Maps Platform (two-key pattern).
- **Production topology:** three Cloud Run services (`api`, `push-worker`, `sweeper`); GCP Cloud SQL HA Standard tier; Memorystore Redis Basic; Global External ALB + Cloud Armor; all in `australia-southeast1`.
- **Pub/Sub topics:** `member-status`, `member-location`, `callout-events` (each with DLQ).
- **Auth:** LIMSOC JWT (HS256) for VIC year 1; SLSA Members Area adapter for national next.
- **Tenant isolation:** AsyncLocalStorage + `withTenantContextAsync` + static analyser. Default DENY on `state_cross_org_configs` when config row is missing.
- **LIMSOC credential shape:** `linked_credentials` table binds Firebase UID to SLSA `member_id`. Token stored AES-256-GCM (`CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPTION_KEY`). Awards adapter must treat a 404 as an empty list before throwing `UpstreamError`.
- **Reliability targets:** Year 1 ~3.5-nines, architected for 4-nines. P95 push < 5s, P99 < 10s. P95 API write < 200ms, P99 < 500ms.
- **DB migrations:** 0001-0029 applied to `loc-postgres`; `dev` tip `693cfc7`. No pending migrations locally.
- **Never** use `--set-env-vars` on Cloud Run; always `--update-env-vars`.
- **`NEXT_PUBLIC_*`** are Docker build args baked at build time; pass as ARG+ENV in Dockerfile and `args` in compose `build:` block.
- **Docker Compose:** always `docker compose --env-file .env.local`; never `.env.local` auto-read by compose.
- **Worktree pattern:** one worktree per branch under `lifesaveroncall-wt/<branch-name>/`; commit local fixes before firing any agent.
- **Idempotency keys** on every state-changing API call.
- Australian English throughout; all data resident in `australia-southeast1`.

## Goal

LifesaverOnCall reaches production with at least one LSV pilot tenant: LIMSOC credential integration verified end-to-end, dispatch and incident lifecycle complete, mobile responder app functional, GCP infrastructure provisioned via Terraform, and the hard Phase 4 blockers cleared. Done is measured by: at least one real responder paged and accepted via the app in a controlled pilot environment, with a complete audit trail, no PII leakage, and no expired-award dispatch.

